Option A — left part translated, keep rest unchanged
- Translate only the leftmost term before the dot to German, and leave the part after the dot as is.
Option B — full German phrases (one term) for every header
- Provide a single German term for each header, collapsing any dot paths into one natural German label.
- alternate_bases.AC -> Alternativbasen_AC (or a single word like AlternativbasenAC)
Option C — maintain original tokens for safety
- Translate only the clearly translatable words and keep all technical tokens (AC, AF, vep, etc.) exactly as in the source, resulting in mixed-language headers that remain machine-parseable.
Which option would you prefer? If you’d like, I can start by applying your chosen approach to the first 20 headers as a sample.
